title: Echo wins Queen's Wharf tender in Brisbane
text:
Mon, Jul 20, 2015, 6:28 PM AEST - Australia Markets closed Echo wins Queen's Wharf tender in Brisbane AAP – 46 minutes ago Print 
Echo Entertainment has won the right to develop the prime riverfront land of the Queen's Wharf precinct in Brisbane. 
The proposal from Echo, which operates the Treasury Casino in Brisbane, includes an iconic arc-shaped building with a ballroom, publicly accessible sky deck, 50 restaurants and bars, a new lyric theatre at South Bank and a moonlight cinema. 
"We know what this means for Brisbane - making it a premium tourist destination," Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk said on Monday. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook AAP
